# swiftformat configuration for JSONFoundation. Run locally before committing:
#
#   swiftformat .
#
# SwiftFormat's opinionated wrapping / hoisting / self / doc-comment rules are
# disabled to preserve the hand-written structure. What stays enabled is the
# safe, mechanical layer: import order, operator spacing, redundant-whitespace
# and blank-line cleanup.

--swiftversion 6.0
--indent 4
--tabwidth unspecified

# Block-indent continuations of multi-line conditions (matches the hand style).
--wrapconditions after-first

# Disabled rules:
#   trailingCommas / wrapMultilineStatementBraces — conflict with SwiftLint's
#     `trailing_comma` / `opening_brace`.
#   redundantReturn — can break generic inference for
#     `withCheckedThrowingContinuation<T>` in async Void contexts.
#   The remainder reformat the deliberately hand-written structure (one-line
#     bodies, argument wrapping, `case .x(let y)` placement, explicit `self`,
#     explicit Sendable, regular vs. doc comments) and are left as-is.
--disable trailingCommas,wrapMultilineStatementBraces,redundantReturn,wrapArguments,wrapFunctionBodies,wrapPropertyBodies,wrapLoopBodies,indent,hoistPatternLet,hoistTry,docComments,conditionalAssignment,redundantSelf,redundantSendable,blankLinesBetweenScopes,extensionAccessControl,opaqueGenericParameters,unusedArguments,andOperator

--exclude .build,.swiftpm
